Read in all the dialogue from Goodfellas

good <- read.csv("goodfellas.csv", header = F)
good1 <- paste(good, collapse = " ")
good2 <- data.frame(word = unlist(str_split(good1, " ")))
clean <- function(x) {
    x <- gsub("-", " ", x)
    x <- tolower(x)
    x <- replace_contraction(x)
    x <- gsub("\\d+(st|nd|rd|th)", " ", x)
    x <- gsub("[^a-zA-Z]", " ", x)  #strips any non-alphabetic characters including numbers and punctuation
    x <- gsub("\\b[a-zA-Z]\\b{1}", " ", x)
    x <- removeWords(x, stopwords(source = "smart"))
    x <- stripWhitespace(x)
    x <- stri_remove_empty(x)
    x <- data.frame(x)
    x <- str_split(x, " ")
    x <- unlist(x)
}
good3 <- clean(good2)

# remove rows with NA

trysmooth <- onlyvals %>%
    mutate(smootharouse = zoo::rollmean(Arousal, k = 5, fill = NA))  #smooth using rolling mean
# smooth the arousal time series
colvec <- c("gray", "green")
goodplot <- ggplot(trysmooth, aes(x = Order, y = smootharouse, fill = Condition)) +
    geom_col(position = "dodge") + scale_fill_manual(values = colvec) + jamie.theme
ggsave("luciagoodfellasplot.pdf")
